cs.CY, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.HC 

This paper focuses on understanding communication patterns in MOOCs using data mining and qualitative methods. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 

- cs.CY (Computers and Society): This sub-category deals with the social and ethical aspects of computing, including the impact of technology on education and learning. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This sub-category deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics, which are relevant to analyzing communication patterns in MOOCs. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category deals with developing algorithms and models for analyzing large datasets, which is relevant to the data mining aspect of this paper. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): This sub-category deals with the analysis of social networks and online communities, which is relevant to understanding communication patterns in MOOCs. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): This sub-category deals with the design and evaluation of interactive systems, which is relevant to the qualitative methods aspect of this paper.
